        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 4 at 9:20PM CDT until April 4 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 920 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles east of
Broken Bow, or 15 miles west of De Queen, moving north at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Plunketville, Broken Bow, Holly Creek, Smithville,
Hochatown, Watson, Oak Hill, and Idabel.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
